## Rules

### TEST-001: Jest/Vitest Structure
severity: ERROR
scope: all test files
rule: Test files MUST use describe/it blocks with descriptive names. Each test MUST call at least one expect assertion. Tests MUST NOT use done callbacks — async tests MUST return a Promise or use async/await.
threshold: min_coverage_pct=80, max_test_file_lines=300
example_correct: |
  describe('OrderService', () => {
    it('returns error when order is invalid', async () => {
      const result = await service.process({});
      expect(result.ok).toBe(false);
    });
  });
example_incorrect: |
  test('test1', (done) => {
    service.process({}, (err) => { done(); });  // callback pattern
  });

### TEST-002: Mock Isolation
severity: ERROR
scope: all unit test files
rule: Unit tests MUST mock all external dependencies. Tests MUST NOT make real HTTP requests or database calls. jest.mock() MUST be reset between tests using afterEach or beforeEach.
threshold: min_coverage_pct=80
example_correct: |
  jest.mock('../repository');
  beforeEach(() => { jest.clearAllMocks(); });
example_incorrect: |
  // Making real HTTP requests in unit tests — prohibited
